[Method]
DrawHatchRect
[Prefix]
Odcl_PictureBox_
[Desc]
This method draws a hatched rectangle on the control. There are five styles of windows hatches available, an integer of 1 - 5 will indicate which one is to be drawn. \par
\par \b Hatch Pattern Flags:
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 \b Flag\tab Description\b0 
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 1 \tab Vertical lines.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 2 \tab Right slanted lines.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 3 \tab Left slanted lines.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 4 \tab Horizontal, vertical grid pattern.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 5 \tab Diagonal grid pattern.	

\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab UpperLeftX
[as Integer]
\par\tab UpperLeftY
[as Integer]
\par\tab Width
[as Integer]
\par\tab Height
[as Integer]
\par\tab LineColor
[as Integer]
\par\tab HatchPattern
[as Integer]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]



[Method]
DrawEdge
[Prefix]
Odcl_PictureBox_
[Desc]
This method draws various standard windows control borders. Color control is automatically handled by this method.\par
\par \b Border Flags:
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 \b Flag\tab Description\b0 
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 1 \tab Raised Inner-border.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 2 \tab Sunken inner-border.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 3 \tab Raised outer-border.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 4 \tab Edge bump.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 5 \tab Edge etched.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 6 \tab Edge raised.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 7 \tab Edge sunken.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab UpperLeftX
[as Integer]
\par\tab UpperLeftY
[as Integer]
\par\tab Width
[as Integer]
\par\tab Height
[as Integer]
\par\tab BorderFlag
[as Integer]
\par\tab [End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]




[Method]
DrawFocusRect
[Prefix]
Odcl_PictureBox_
[Desc]
This method draws a focus rectangle used to indicate the control has focus. This method is a Boolean XOR function, calling this function a second time with the same rectangle removes the rectangle from the display. 
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab UpperLeftX
[as Integer]
\par\tab UpperLeftY
[as Integer]
\par\tab Width
[as Integer]
\par\tab Height
[as Integer]
\par\tab [End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]



